The paper focuses on tracking multiple objects in an urban environment using computer vision techniques. Specifically, it proposes a model-based vehicle localization method that utilizes shape fitness evaluation and color information to track vehicle objects. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also implements evolutionary camera self-calibration and object detection/classification, which could fall under the robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
